either serving part time in the Army National Guard or Army Reserve  or full time on active duty  Non scholarship students have no obligation until your sophomore year in college  Once you decide to contract  your military obligation is as follows  Active Duty Scholarship cadets  8 Year Commitment  4 years Active Duty 4 years Additional of Active Duty  Reserve Forces duty or a combination of both   Active Duty Non Scholarship cadets  8 Year Commitment  3 years of Active Duty 5 years additional of Active Duty  Reserve Forces duty or a combination of both   Dedicated National Guard or Reserve Scholarship 8 Year Commitment  6 years of  M Day  service  1 weekend per month  2 weeks of Annual Training during the summer 2 years additional service   M day or Inactive National Guard  ING  or Inactive Ready Reserve  IRR    For more information contact  Maj  Lloyd Wells Phone   540  464 7818 Email  wellsld10 vmi edu Mr  Thomas Atkinson Phone   540  464 7680 Email  atkinsonte vmi edu   VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 